<phone-release>
	<release-header>
		<name>August 09, 2016 H323 96xx 3.2.7 GA</name>
		<date>2016-08-09</date>
		<description>Copyright Avaya Inc. 2016 All rights reserved. This file describes the contents of the August 2016 software distribution package for the 96XX H323 IP Telephones.  The reason for the release of this software is:     - The R3.2.7  Version of 96xx H323 Software for 9620L, 9620C, 9630G, 9640, 9640G, 9650, 9650C and 9670G Telephones.  There is one firmware version with multiple language files in this distribution package. All these files are available in a zip folder. This release supports an upgrade strategy for H323 software.   The following files are included in all packages: 96xxupgrade.txt - This file is downloaded by the Avaya IP telephones and instructs each telephone on how to upgrade itself. This file SHOULD NOT BE EDITED. System specific parameters should be entered into the 46xxsettings.txt file, which is available for separate download at support.avaya.com.  To upgrade your Avaya IP Telephones:   - Rename your current 96xxupgrade.txt file.   - Unzip the zip in the outbound file directory of your HTTP server, as appropriate.   - Make any adjustments to your 46xxsettings.txt file.   - Reset your Avaya IP Telephones.</description>
	</release-header>
